main event: An unidentified object was observed on radar over the Atlantic Ocean on May 31, 1963.
interesting points: The radar detected four returns from an object with a flight path changeable, with speeds recorded at 1400 mph., No visual sightings were made despite the object appearing on radar at ranges of 2, 3.5, and 5 miles., The sighting lasted around three minutes., The possibility of equipment malfunction or electronic interference was mentioned., The report included radar film for analysis and was part of Project Blue Book.
witness description: crew members on the MSTS Ship Pvt. Joe E. Mann
